Generate a BPMN definition object from the validated process contract.

The validated ProcessContract is the primary and authoritative generation input.
Use the original input only as secondary traceability context.

Contract-driven generation rules:
- Include the contract trigger, ordered activities, decisions, branches, exception or rework paths, and end states.
- Generate exactly one START_EVENT node for `contract.start`. Put trigger semantics in that node's `eventDefinition`, not in a specialized start-event subtype.
- `ContractTrigger.Timer` maps to `BpmnTimerEventDefinition`; `Message` maps to `BpmnMessageEventDefinition` plus a process-level `BpmnMessageRef`; `Signal` maps to `BpmnSignalEventDefinition` plus a process-level `BpmnSignalRef`.
- `ContractTrigger.None` maps to `BpmnNoneEventDefinition`.
- ContractIntermediateThrow entries map to `INTERMEDIATE_THROW_EVENT` nodes. `Message` maps to `BpmnMessageEventDefinition` plus a process-level `BpmnMessageRef`; `Signal` maps to `BpmnSignalEventDefinition` plus a process-level `BpmnSignalRef`; `Escalation` maps to `BpmnEscalationEventDefinition` plus a process-level `BpmnEscalationRef`.
- Represent actors only where current BPMN DTOs allow, usually in task names.
- Do not add unsupported tasks, decisions, branches, actors, or end states.
- You may infer sequence flows and routing-only converging gateways needed for valid BPMN.
- Leave routing-only converging gateways unnamed.

Contract-to-BPMN wiring (the schema covers each `kind` â†’ BPMN `type`/`eventDefinition` mapping and the catalogue dedup rules; these are the contract links it can't express):
- BusinessRule: copy `decisionName` from the contract verbatim into `decisionRef` on the BPMN node.
- Send / Receive: point the task's `messageRef` at a `definition.messages` entry whose `name` is the contract's `messageName`.
- Iteration â†’ multi-instance: when a contract activity carries `iteration`, set `multiInstance` on its BPMN task â€” `mode` = the contract's `iteration.mode` (SEQUENTIAL renders `isSequential=true`, PARALLEL renders `isSequential=false`), `collectionDescription` = the contract's verbatim. ALSO emit, for that task: (1) a `definition.annotations` text annotation whose text names the item set using "each"/"every"/"per" (e.g. "For each line item on the slip"), and (2) a `definition.associations` edge with `sourceRef` = the task id and `targetRef` = that annotation's id. Every multi-instance task MUST have this linked annotation.
- Boundary events â†’ boundary-event nodes: when a contract activity carries `boundaryEvents`, emit one `BOUNDARY_EVENT` node per entry with `attachedToRef` = that activity's BPMN task id and `cancelActivity` from the contract. Map `kind`: TIMER â†’ `BpmnTimerEventDefinition` whose expression is the contract `detail` (an ISO-8601 duration); ERROR â†’ `BpmnErrorEventDefinition` pointing at a `definition.errors` entry whose `code` is the contract `detail`; ESCALATION â†’ `BpmnEscalationEventDefinition` pointing at a `definition.escalations` entry whose `code` is the contract `detail`. Emit exactly one outbound sequence flow from the boundary event to the node whose id is `nextRef`, with no incoming flow into it. For ERROR boundary events, `cancelActivity` is true.
- Loop â†’ standard-loop: when a contract activity carries `loop`, set `standardLoop` on its BPMN task â€” `testBefore` from the contract (true = while, false = until), `loopCondition` and `loopMaximum` copied verbatim. ALSO emit, for that task: (1) a `definition.annotations` text annotation whose text states the loop condition using "until"/"while"/"unless"/"till" (e.g. "Retry until the payment succeeds"), and (2) a `definition.associations` edge with `sourceRef` = the task id and `targetRef` = that annotation's id. Every standard-loop task has this linked annotation. Treat `loop` as a self-repeating task; reserve gateway back-edges for explicit branch flows.
- Data artifacts â†’ data objects/stores: emit one `definition.dataObjects` entry for each contract artifact whose kind is DATA_OBJECT, and one `definition.dataStores` entry for each DATA_STORE, copying the artifact id and name verbatim. Then for each activity, emit one `definition.dataAssociations` edge per `dataInputIds` id (sourceRef = activity id, targetRef = data id, direction = READ) and per `dataOutputIds` id (direction = WRITE). Keep data names as business nouns (e.g. "Order", "Customer database").
- Error / Message / Signal / Escalation end states: point the event definition's ref at a matching entry in the process-level `definition.errors` / `.messages` / `.signals` / `.escalations` catalogue whose `code`/`name` is the contract's.
- Message / Signal / Escalation intermediate throws: point the event definition's ref at a matching entry in the process-level `definition.messages` / `.signals` / `.escalations` catalogue whose `name`/`code` is the contract's.

Branch wiring (the `kind` â†’ BpmnEdge shape is in each ContractBranch subtype's schema, and `conditionExpression`/`isDefault` carry their own field descriptions):
- DEFAULT: emit the outbound edge with no `conditionExpression`. You may leave `isDefault = false`; the downstream DefaultFlowAssigner sets it from the contract and the renderer writes the gateway's `default="Flow_X"` attribute. NEVER invent placeholder conditions like "otherwise" or "all other cases".

